Welcome to the study!

Your participation will help us investigate human precision and reaction-times.

Please read the instructions carefully.

Press the space bar to continue

stimulus:
In order to begin, we first need to measure the size of your screen and the distance you are sitting from it.

This will allow us to calibrate the experiment's presentation size specifically for you.

After this short calibration, we will continue with the main task of this study.

Press the space bar to continue

stimulus:

We ask you to not change this throughout the whole course of the experiment.

stimulus:
In this part you will be asked to find a single flickering object within a scene. Each time you will be presented with one scene. This scene will be static, except for one single object that will be appearing and disappearing. Your goal will be to detect this object as quickly and accurately as you can. We will ask you to place your finger over the space bar, and once you have found the object press the space bar as quickly as possible.

For each scene, you will have 60 seconds to do so. After that you will be asked about the location of the object.

We will now continue with a short practice before starting the main task.

Press the space bar to continue

stimulus:
In this part you will be asked to find a single flickering object within a scene. Each time you will be presented with one scene. This scene will be static, except for one single object that will be appearing and disappearing. Your goal will be to detect this object as quickly and accurately as you can. We will ask you to place your finger over the space bar, and once you have found the object press the space bar as quickly as possible.

For each scene, you will have 60 seconds to do so. After that you will be asked about the location of the object.

We will now continue with a short practice before starting the main task.
